title: For Sale:  STEYR HAHN MODEL 1912  9MM SEMI AUTO PISTOL (MFD. 1917)
postcontent: Single Action Semi-Auto Pistol with Internal Magazine Fed by Stripper Clips. Austrian Army issue M12, has STEYR 1917 (date) on the left rear of the slide. Dovetailed front sight. The left side of the slide is marked “STEYR 1917”, “S”. The left side of the hammer and the frame in front of the safety are marked “K”. The right side of the frame above the trigger is marked “W-n” (Wiener-Neustadt), a Hapsburg Eagle, and a “17” date code. It does have the "08" proof mark on the left side. Some of these pistols were converted to fire 9x19 Luger (9mm P.Patr.08) ammunition, and issued to a variety of German 2nd line military troops and police. Such pistols were usually marked on the slide with "08" or "P-08", to distinguish them from original guns chambered for 9x23 Steyr ammunition. NOTE: It is unknown if this particular gun has been converted to 9mm Luger, but the "08" proof mark is present.
